  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels. Some key examples include:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset seizure and criminal prosecution\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Monitor and report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain detailed transaction records\n- Implement internal compliance programs\n- Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nThe goal is to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
